HEADWORD: Sitter
<hw>Sit"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who
sits; esp., one who sits for a portrait or a bust.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A bird that sits or incubates.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Sittine</ent>⟦br⟧
